

- an object which contains elements of a similar data type
- stored in contiguous memory location
- can store only a fixed set of elements in array
- index-based, first element of the array is stored at 0th index
- variables in the array are ordered


Advantages:
1. code optimization
2. Random access

Disadvantage:
1. size limit

Types of Array
1. Single Dimensional Array
	Syntax:
		datatype[] var_name; OR
		datatype []var_name; OR
		datatype var_name[];

2. Multidimensional Array
	Syntax:
		datatype[][] var_name; OR
		datatype [][]var_name; OR
		datatype var_name[][]; OR
		datatype []var_name[];

Jagged Array
	- creating odd number of columns
	- an array of arrays with diff no of columns





